hh3cMPortGroupJoinTable.name: hh3cMPortGroupJoinTable
hh3cMPortGroupJoinTable.description: A table which is used for configuring a port in a specified VLAN to join a multicast group.

hh3cMPortGroupJoinEntry.name: hh3cMPortGroupJoinEntry
hh3cMPortGroupJoinEntry.description: An entry which is used for configuring a port in a specified VLAN to join a multicast group.

hh3cMPortGroupJoinVlanID.name: hh3cMPortGroupJoinVlanID
hh3cMPortGroupJoinVlanID.description: An index uniquely identifying a port in a specified VLAN which joined the multicast group.

hh3cMPortGroupJoinAddressType.name: hh3cMPortGroupJoinAddressType
hh3cMPortGroupJoinAddressType.description: Type of the multicast IP address.

hh3cMPortGroupJoinAddress.name: hh3cMPortGroupJoinAddress
hh3cMPortGroupJoinAddress.description: IP address of the group which the port belongs to, and it must be a valid multicast IP address.

hh3cMPortGroupJoinStatus.name: hh3cMPortGroupJoinStatus
hh3cMPortGroupJoinStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation and deletion of rows, which supports 'active', 'notReady', 'createAndGo', 'destroy'. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the hh3cMPortGroupJoinStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be actived until the port belongs to the corresponding VLAN and IGMP or IGMP snooping is enabled on that VLAN.

hh3cMPortGroupTable.name: hh3cMPortGroupTable
hh3cMPortGroupTable.description: A table containing information about the status of a port which joined a multicast group in the VLAN.

hh3cMPortGroupEntry.name: hh3cMPortGroupEntry
hh3cMPortGroupEntry.description: An entry containing information about the status of a port which joined a multicast group in the VLAN.

hh3cMPortGroupVlanID.name: hh3cMPortGroupVlanID
hh3cMPortGroupVlanID.description: An index uniquely identifies that a port belongs to a specified VLAN.

hh3cMPortGroupAddress.name: hh3cMPortGroupAddress
hh3cMPortGroupAddress.description: IP address of the group which the port joined, and it must be a valid multicast IP address.

hh3cMPortConfigTable.name: hh3cMPortConfigTable

hh3cMPortConfigEntry.name: hh3cMPortConfigEntry
hh3cMPortConfigEntry.description: An entry containing information about the fast leave status, group limit number and group policy parameter of a port in the specified VLAN.

hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber.name: hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber
hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber.description: The group limit number of the port.

hh3cMPortFastLeaveStatus.name: hh3cMPortFastLeaveStatus
hh3cMPortFastLeaveStatus.description: The fast leave status of the port.

hh3cMPortGroupPolicyParameter.name: hh3cMPortGroupPolicyParameter
hh3cMPortGroupPolicyParameter.description: The ACL number which is used as the group policy parameter of the port.

hh3cMPortConfigRowStatus.name: hh3cMPortConfigRowStatus
hh3cMPortConfigRowStatus.description: The object is responsible for managing the creation and deletion of rows, which supports 'active', 'notReady', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.

hh3cMPortGroupLimitReplace.name: hh3cMPortGroupLimitReplace
hh3cMPortGroupLimitReplace.description: This object is related to the object hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber. If the current IGMP group number is less than the value of hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber, any new IGMP group is permitted. If the current IGMP group number equals to the value of hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber and the value of this object is enabled, the group with the minimum multicast address will be replaced by the new group. If the current IGMP group number equals to the value of hh3cMPortGroupLimitNumber and the value of this object is disabled, none of new group will be permitted.

hh3cHostStaticJoinTable.name: hh3cHostStaticJoinTable

hh3cHostStaticJoinEntry.name: hh3cHostStaticJoinEntry

hh3cHostStaticJoinVlanID.name: hh3cHostStaticJoinVlanID

hh3cHostStaticJoinAddressType.name: hh3cHostStaticJoinAddressType
hh3cHostStaticJoinAddressType.description: Type of the multicast IP address.

hh3cHostStaticJoinAddress.name: hh3cHostStaticJoinAddress
hh3cHostStaticJoinAddress.description: IP address of the group which the host belongs to, and it must be a valid multicast IP address.

hh3cHostStaticJoinStatus.name: hh3cHostStaticJoinStatus
hh3cHostStaticJoinStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing rows, which supports 'active', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.
